<head>
<title>Thompson Speech</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg">
<center>
<i>July 26, 1995</i>
<hr>
<br>
<h3>SCHOOL CHOICE RALLY 
MESSMER HIGH SCHOOL 
MILWAUKEE, WISCONSIN </h3><p>
<h2>A Speech by Gov. Tommy G Thompson of Wisconsin</h2>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
THANK YOU, BROTHER BOB. <p>
WHAT A DAY! <p>
 THIS MORNING I SIGNED INTO LAW THE MOST  
REVOLUTIONARY BUDGET IN OUR STATE'S HISTORY ... <p>
 AND THIS AFTERNOON WE ARE HER; TO CELEBRATE ONE OF  
THE MOST REVOLUTIONARY PARTS OF THAT BUDGET ... THE  
EXPANSION OF THE MILWAUKEE PARENTAL SCHOOL CHOICE  
PLAN. <p> 
"REVOLUTIONARY" IS NOT OVER-STATING THE CASE: THE  
MILWAUKEE SCHOOL CHOICE PROGRAM WAS "THE SHOT  
HEARD ROUND THE WORLD." WE WERE THE FIRST. <p> 
AND NOW OTHERS ARE FOLLOWING OUR LEAD ... OHIO IS  
STARTING SCHOOL CHOICE IN CLEVELAND ... WASHINGTON  
D.C. IS TALKING ABOUT A VOUCHER PROGRAM. <p> 
(YOU KNOW YOU'RE MAKING PROGRESS WHEN WE  
WASHINGTON POST FINALLY ADMITS YOU MIGHT  
ACTUALLY HAVE A GOOD IDEA.) <p> 
WHAT SCHOOL CHOICE IS DOING, LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,  
IS VERY SIMPLE: IT IS REDEFINING PUBLIC EDUCATION.  <p> 
PUBLIC SCHOOLS MUST NO LONGER BE GOVERNMENT-RUN 
SCHOOLS. THEY WILL BE SCHOOLS THAT SERVE THE PUBLIC.  <p> 
SCHOOL CHOICE IS MORE THAN A PROGRAM .. IT IS A  
PHILOSOPHY. <p>
IT IS THE BELIEF THAT PARENTS KNOW BEST WHEN IT COMES  
TO THEIR CHILDREN ... <p> 
AND IT IS THE BELIEF THAT POOR PARENTS HAVE THE SAME  
RIGHT TO CHOOSE THAT OTHER PARENTS DO. <p> 
THAT'S EDUCATION THAT IS SERVING THE PUBLIC. <p> 
WHY SHOULD WE BUS OUR CHILDREN ACROSS TOWN WHEN  
THERE ARE PERFECTLY GOOD SCHOOLS RIGHT IN THEIR OWN  
NEIGHBORHOODS? SCHOOLS LIKE MESSMER. <p> 
THAT DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE. AND IT ALSO DOESN'T  
MAKE ANY SENSE TO CROSS VERY GOOD SCHOOLS OFF THE  
LIST SIMPLY BECAUSE THEY HAVE A RELIGIOUS 
AFFILIATION.<p> 
RELIGIOUS VALUES ARE NOT OUR PROBLEM, LADIES AND 
GENTLEMAN, DROP-OUT RATES ARE. <p> 
I AM NOT NAIVE. I KNOW WE ARE GOING TO FACE A FIGHT  
ON THIS. <p> 
BUT I ALSO KNOW WE ARE GOING TO WIN ... BECAUSE WE 
ARE RIGHT! <p> 
OUR OPPONENTS WILL THROW UP SMOKE SCREENS. THEY'LL  
SAY THE ISSUE HERE IS THE SEPARATION OF CHURCH AND   
STATE. <p> 
LET ME TELL YOU WHAT THE ISSUE IS HERE -- TO MAKE SURE  
MILWAUKEE SCHOOL CHILDREN RECEIVE THE BEST  
EDUCATION POSSIBLE... PERIOD. <p> 
THAT'S THE ISSUE ... THAT'S WHY WE ARE HERE TODAY ...  
AND THAT'S WHY WE WILL WIN ANY COURT BATTLES THEY  
THROW IN OUR WAY. <p> 
ONE-THIRD OF MILWAUKEE PUBLIC SCHOOL TEACHERS SEND  
THEIR CHILDREN TO PRIVATE SCHOOLS. <p> 
IT SEEMS TO ME WHAT'S GOOD ENOUGH FOR THEM OUGHT  
TO BE GOOD ENOUGH FOR ALL OF YOU. <p>
THE PHONES ARE RINGING OFF THE HOOK. THOUSANDS OF  
PARENTS HAVE ALREADY CALLED TO MY "GIVE US A  
CHANCE ... GIVE US A CHOICE." <p> 
MEANTIME, OUR OPPONENTS ARE FIGHTING US. THEY'RE  
GOING TO SPEND THEIR MONEY ... THEY'RE GOING TO SUE ...  
THEY'RE GOING TO STAND IN THE WAY OF CHANGE. <p> 
THEY CAN AFFORD TO ... THEY ALREADY HAVE THE CHOICE. <p> 
SO TODAY, WE ARE LEVELING THE PLAYING FIELD. <p> 
WE ARE SAYING IT DOESN'T MATTER IF YOU LIVE ON LAKE  
DRIVE ... OR 35TH AND NORTH ... <p> 
YOU ARE GOING TO HAVE THE RIGHT TO CHOOSE THE BEST  
SCHOOL FOR YOUR OWN CHILD. <p> 
TOGETHER, YOU AND I HAVE TURNED MILWAUKEE INTO THE  
LEXINGTON AND CONCORD OF THE EDUCATION REFORM  
BATTLEFRONT. <p>
TODAY, WE ARE TAKING THE NEXT STEP. EVERYONE IS  
LOOKING TO US. <p> 
LETS SHOW THEM WHAT WE'VE GOT! <p>
THANK YOU. <p>
<a href="welcome.html.cgi">Introduction</a>
</body>
