2.  In the formula for first-year funding under Goals 2000, a state is required to offer competitive subgrants to local education agencies with 60 percent of the total state grant.  Local education agencies must then pass on 75 percent of their monies to local schools. See section 308(a)(1) and section 309(a)(6).  <p>
3.  Richard W. Riley, "Goals 2000: Educate America Act.  Providing a World-Class Education for Every Child,"  National Issues in Education:  Goals 2000 and School-to-Work 5-6.  <p>
4.  One example is:  William J. Bennett, The Index of Leading Cultural Indicators:  Facts and Figures on the State of American Society (New York:  Simon & Schuster, 1994) 82.<p>
