<html>
<head>
<title>RNC Talking Points - Medicare</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg">
<center><h2>RNC Talking Points</h2></center><br>
<center><h4>The GOP Plan to Save Medicare -- The Time Is Now</h4></center>
<hr>
The GOP Medicare Preservation Act provides that:<br>
<ul>
<li>The traditional form of fee-for-service Medicare will continue to be an option for all beneficiaries -- no senior will be forced to give up his or her current Medicare coverage.<p>
<li>Total Medicare spending will increase by 54 percent over the next seven years.  Average spending per senior will increase 40 percent from today's $4,800 to more that $6,700 in 2002.<p>
<li>Seniors will have the right to choose from several health care plans similar to those available to other Americans in the private sector.
<ul>
<P>
The GOP reforms must be enacted now.  If not, the Part A trust fund will be bankrupt in 2002--just seven years from now.<p>
The GOP has the only plan to save Medicare<p>
</DOC>
